telemetry.userPrompt: Build a cool learning experience for a seven-year-old advanced first grader to learn about our solar system with the ability to zoom in to all the planets and see every stat about their size and everything. Add a funny dad joke per planet too.
telemetry.researchPlan:
TOPIC: Our Solar System — An Interactive Space Explorer for Kids
AUDIENCE: 7-year-old advanced first grader
PLANETS: All 8 + Sun + Pluto
GROUPING: Inner Rocky vs Outer Giants
KEY STATS: Distance, diameter, day/year length, gravity, temperature, moons, atmosphere, fun facts, dad jokes, exploration history
SECTIONS: Mission Control, Planet Explorer, Space Records (7 sub-tabs), Size Showdown, Hot & Cold, Gravity Playground, Race to the Sun, Earth Moon & Seasons, Night Sky, Space Events, Space Timeline, Trivia Game, Space Lab, Space Library
INTERACTIVES: Wind Race Game, Time Converter, Spinning Planet Comparator, Gravity Calculator, Distance Race, Constellation Viewer, Trivia Game

contentAnalysis.readabilityNote: Kid-friendly space exploration with interactive games, animated comparisons, real-world analogies, and hands-on learning for a 7-year-old audience. Includes wind speed race game, planet time converter, spinning planet comparator, and rich record book.
